# Disable the JVM optimisation that drops stacktrace frames from repeated
# exceptions (e.g. NullPointerException).  Without this flag, high-frequency
# exceptions produce a single-line stacktrace ("java.lang.NullPointerException\n")
# which makes the OpenTelemetry exception.stacktrace span attribute useless for
# root-cause analysis.
#
# This flag applies to Maven itself when using ./mvnw.  For the running
# application, add -XX:-OmitStackTraceInFastThrow to the JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS
# environment variable (or to run.sh, which is gitignored):
#
#   export JAVA_TOOL_OPTIONS="-XX:-OmitStackTraceInFastThrow -javaagent:opentelemetry-javaagent.jar"
-XX:-OmitStackTraceInFastThrow
